laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Hamilton scores decreased from 30 to 10 after 1 week of phototherapy, then increased to 26 with melatonin, and further increased to 32 with placebo.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Melatonin levels were unusually low compared to published normal values.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: There was no significant difference in melatonin profiles between the baseline follicular and premenstrual phases.

laboratory_examinations.findings: TSH levels showed significant variation based on condition but were not significantly different between follicular and premenstrual phases.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: There were significant main effects observed in conditions but no significant Time of Day by Condition interaction.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Prolactin was 19.05 ± 2.05 ng/ml during the follicular phase and 9.22 ± 3.54 ng/ml during the premenstrual phase.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Prolactin levels were significantly higher during the follicular phase than premenstrual phase.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Estradiol levels were obtained but specific results not detailed.
Indicated ovulation with values > 5 ng/ml in the luteal phase.
